text: Alex Dupont (30 June 1954 – 1 August 2020) was a French football manager and former player. He coached Dunkerque, Charleville, Boulogne, Gueugnon, with whom he won the Coupe de la Ligue in 2000, Sedan, Laval, Amiens. He managed Brest from 2009 to 2012, when he took over from Gérald Baticle, and from 2013 to 2016.
